'''Ōbe Shrine''' (おおべじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in Ōbe, {{ill|lt=Kawanishi|Q609350|WD=Q609350|1=Kawanishi, Hyōgo}}, {{ill|lt=Hyōgo Prefecture|Q130290|WD=Q130290|1=Hyōgo Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} of {{ill|lt=Kawabe District|Q1042053|WD=Q1042053|lt=Kōbe District|1=Kawabe District, Hyōgo}}, {{ill|lt=Settsu Province|Q864163|WD=Q864163|1=Settsu Province}}. In the '{{ill|lt=Tokusen Jinmyōchō|Q11571092|WD=Q11571092|1=Tokusen Jinmyōchō}}' it is read "Obe," but today it is called "Ōbe."

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|WD=Q386563|lt=Ōyamatsumi|Q386563|WD=Q386563|WD=Q386563|lt=Ōyamatsumi-no-Mikoto|1=Ōyamatsumi}}
* {{ill|lt=Susanoo|Q272993|WD=Q272993|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}}
* {{ill|lt=Ame-no-Koyane|Q2564508|WD=Q2564508|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane}}

=== History ===
In the '{{ill|lt=Settsu meisho zue|Q11498549|WD=Q11498549|1=Settsu Meisho Zue}}' it says: "Located in Ōbe village. Appears in the '{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|lt=Engishiki (Register of Deities)|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}.' It is the ubusuna deity of Ōbe, Sakaine, Kobana and others." It was revered as the {{ill|lt=ubusunagami|Q1392097|WD=Q1392097|1=Ubusunagami}} over the west bank area of the {{ill|lt=Inagawa River|Q11571867|WD=Q11571867|1=Ina River}}.
* In August of {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 6 ({{ill|lt=1873|Q7757|WD=Q7757|1=1873}}), it became a {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.
* In Meiji 42 ({{ill|lt=1909|Q2057|WD=Q2057|1=1909}}), Yasaka Shrine and Hosokawa-hime Shrine were merged.
* In {{ill|lt=Shōwa|Q327567|WD=Q327567|1=Shōwa era}} 42 ({{ill|lt=1967|Q2648|WD=Q2648|1=1967}}), a new {{ill|lt=honden|Q2044994|WD=Q2044994|1=Honden}} was built.
* In {{ill|lt=Heisei|Q234510|WD=Q234510|1=Heisei era}} 20 ({{ill|lt=2008|Q2004|WD=Q2004|1=2008}}), it was repaired<ref>Sadatoshi Yoshii, "Ōbe Shrine" ("Shikinaisha Survey Report", Vol. 5, Kōgakkan University Press, 1977) {{全国書誌番号|78005760}}</ref>.

=== Precinct shrines ===

* Fujimori Shrine - Ōtsuki-hime-no-Mikoto
* Inari Shrine - {{ill|lt=Hakuryū Ōkami|Q123407570|WD=Q123407570|1=Hakuryū Ōkami}}
* Kashima Shrine - {{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q1502690|lt=Takemikazuchi-no-Kami|1=Takemikazuchi}}
